Author: buzzer9229
Content: Attack on Titan is more philosophical and cerebral than Code Geass. Attack on Titan is like on the same level of Death Note that its a thinking man's action anime. Attack on Titan explores themes of racism, warfare, civilization and history. Not saying that Code Geass explores almost the same themes of racism, warfare but with colonialism, exploitation and ambition, but Attack on Titan focuses mostly on the systematic, ideological and philosophical aspects. It focuses more on how an individual moves through history like a part of a history of a bigger group of people that interconnects with each other, a person's relationship with their people, their ideology, their race, their tribe, their nation, their history. Meanwhile Code Geass has a more human focus. It centers around people's relationships with each other, character drama and heightened emotions. Attack on Titan is about making history while Code Geass is more about spectacle and awe.

Author: buzzer9229
Content: They are quite similar in themes but just different in execution and focus

Author: buzzer9229
Content: Attack on Titan feels like reading a history book, Code Geass feels like reading a mythic tale

Author: buzzer9229
Content:
@Kader I honestly think that unrest like this will still happen even with Ganjar and Anies yang kepilih. I've already said this multiple of times but belum tentu satu pemerintah dan pemerintahan will FOLLOW what Ganjar and Anies wants to do. I'll explain down below:

1. Ganjar is PDIP and PDIP has a habit of turning the state into a quasi one party state (see Jokowi periode pertama) which means that the opposition will be quite strong and the rhetoric will be how Ganjar is just a puppet for another Megawati dictatorship mastermind control. Citizens who are dissatisfied and players who don't like to see them rule will work in tandem (not cooperate mind you but in tandem) to make sure its not going to be easy. 

2. Anies is a political outlier and a lot of the elites hate him. What I predict will happen if Anies becomes president is two things: 1. either the government will not be effective because Anies lacks the political muscle, meaning nobody wants to be told around by Anies, or 2. Anies will have to pull a Jokowi, forcibly putting his closest people (who aren't necessarily qualified but trustworthy to Anies) into positions of power whom he can trust will secure his regime and have his back, but at the cost of obrak abrik institusi kita.

People seem to think that there will be no problem if we vote Anies or Ganjar. I'd disagree, each presidency we pick different policies and programs and missions and vision, but we also pick problems. Electing Prabowo has the issue of allowing Jokowi to remain supreme and making room for oligarchic control. Tapi permasalah nya ga banyak yang suka ama PDIP and no one will listen to Anies. 

When you pick a president, negara gak automatically will follow what that President wants to do btw (look at Habibie and Gusdur)
